.3.1</span> <span class="toctext">Jugurthine War (111\xe2\x80\x93104 BC)</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-12"><a href="#Celtic_threat_.28121_BC.29_and_Germanic_threat_.28113.E2.80.93101_BC.29"><span class="tocnumber">1.3.2</span> <span class="toctext">Celtic threat (121 BC) and Germanic threat (113\xe2\x80\x93101 BC)</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-13"><a href="#Internal_unrest_.28135.E2.80.9371_BC.29"><span class="tocnumber">1.3.3</span> <span class="toctext">Internal unrest (135\xe2\x80\x9371 BC)</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-14"><a href="#Conflicts_with_Mithridates_.2889.E2.80.9363_BC.29_and_the_Cilician_pirates_.2867_BC.29"><span class="tocnumber">1.3.4</span> <span class="toctext">Conflicts with Mithridates (89\xe2\x80\x9363 BC) and the Cilician pirates (67 BC)</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-15"><a href="#Caesar.27s_early_campaigns_.2859.E2.80.9350_BC.29"><span class="tocnumber">1.3.5</span> <span class="toctext">Caesar\'s early campaigns (59\xe2\x80\x9350 BC)</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-3 tocsection-16"><a href="#Triumvirates_and_Caesarian_ascension_.2853.E2.80.9330_BC.29"><span class="tocnumber">1.3.6</span> <span class="toctext">Triumvirates and Caesarian ascension (53\xe2\x80\x9330 BC)</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class="toclevel-1 tocsection-17"><a href="#Political_history"><span class="tocnumber">2</span> <span class="toctext">Political history</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-18"><a href="#Patrician_era_.28509.E2.80.93367_BC.29"><span class="tocnumber">2.1</span> <span class="toctext">Patrician era (509\xe2\x80\x93367 BC)</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-19"><a href="#Conflict_of_the_Orders_.28367.E2.80.93287_BC.29"><span class="tocnumber">2.2</span> <span class="toctext">Conflict of the Orders (367\xe2\x80\x93287 BC)</span></a></li>\n<li class="toclevel-2 tocsection-20"><a href="#Supremacy_of_the_New_Nobility_.28287.E